# 8. Environment Isolation Strategy

## 8.1 Recommended Enterprise Approach

The platform uses separate Databricks workspaces for each environment.

Recommended environments:

| Environment | Purpose                |
| ----------- | ---------------------- |
| DEV         | Development            |
| QA          | Testing and validation |
| PROD        | Production workloads   |

---

## 8.2 Why Separate Workspaces Per Environment

This approach provides:

* Strong environment isolation
* Reduced operational risk
* Safer production management
* Independent compute configuration
* Independent access control
* Easier CI/CD implementation
* Better audit and governance separation

---

## 8.3 Example Workspace Structure

| Workspace   | Example     |
| ----------- | ----------- |
| Development | holcim-dev  |
| QA          | holcim-qa   |
| Production  | holcim-prod |

---

# 9. S3 Storage Architecture

## 9.1 Recommended Enterprise Storage Design

The recommended approach is:

Separate S3 buckets per environment.

Example:

| Environment | Bucket                |
| ----------- | --------------------- |
| DEV         | s3://holcim-dev-data  |
| QA          | s3://holcim-qa-data   |
| PROD        | s3://holcim-prod-data |

---

## 9.2 Why Separate Buckets Per Environment

Benefits include:

### Security Isolation

Production data remains isolated from non-production environments.

---

### Easier IAM Management

Bucket-level IAM policies simplify access management.

---

### Reduced Production Risk

Prevents accidental modification of production data.

---

### Better Governance

Supports:

* Independent retention policies
* Encryption policies
* Audit policies
* Lifecycle policies

---

### Better Cost Management

Enables separate cost tracking for:

* DEV
* QA
* PROD

---

# 10. Recommended S3 Structure

Within each environment bucket:

| Folder       | Purpose                    |
| ------------ | -------------------------- |
| raw/         | Raw ingestion layer        |
| silver/      | Cleansed/transformed layer |
| gold/        | Business curated layer     |
| checkpoints/ | Streaming checkpoints      |
| logs/        | Operational logs           |

Example:

s3://holcim-prod-data/raw/

s3://holcim-prod-data/silver/

s3://holcim-prod-data/gold/

